<body>
    <h1>Sort Clauses Reference</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout two-right-sidebar" data-layout=3D"two-right-side=
bar">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p><strong>Sort Clauses</strong> are the <em>sorting options</em>&nbsp;for =
Content and Location Search in eZ Platform. For generic use of API Search s=
ee&nbsp;<span class=3D"confluence-link"><a href=3D"#SortClausesReference-Se=
archCriteriaandSortClauses">Search Criteria and Sort Clauses</a></span>.</p=
>
<p>A Sort Clause&nbsp;consists of two parts just like <span class=3D"conflu=
ence-link"><span class=3D"confluence-link">Criterion</span> </span>and Face=
tBuilder:</p>
<ul>
<li>The API Value: <code>SortClause</code></li>
<li>Specific handler per search engine: <code>SortClausesHandler</code></li=
>
</ul>
<p>The&nbsp;<code>SortClause</code>&nbsp;represents the value you use in th=
e API, while <code><span>SortClause</span>Handler</code>&nbsp;deals with th=
e business logic in the background, translating the value to something the =
Search engine can understand.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Implementation&nbsp;and availability of a handler sometimes depends on s=
earch engine&nbsp;capabilities and limitations.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"SortClausesReference-CommonconceptsforallSortClauses">Common conc=
epts for all&nbsp;<span>Sort Clauses&nbsp;</span></h3>
<p>For how to use each and every <span>Sort Clause,</span> see list below a=
s it depends on the <span>Sort Clause</span>&nbsp;Value constructor, but <e=
m>in general</em>&nbsp;you should be aware of the following common concept:=
</p>
<ul>
<li><p><code>sortDirection</code>: The direction to perform the sort, eithe=
r&nbsp;<code><span>Query::<span style=3D"color: rgb(102,14,122);">SORT_ASC<=
/span></span></code><em>(default)</em> or <code> <span>Query::</span> <span=
 style=3D"color: rgb(102,14,122);">SORT_DESC</span></code></p></li>
</ul>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(102,14,122);"><br></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(102,14,122);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">V1.6.0</spa=
n></p>
<p>You can use the method <code>SearchService::getSortClauseFromLocation( L=
ocation $location )</code> to return an array of Sort Clauses that you can =
use on <code>LocationQuery-&gt;sortClauses</code>.</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(102,14,122);"><br></span></p>
<h3 id=3D"SortClausesReference-ListofSortClauses">List of&nbsp;<span>Sort C=
lauses&nbsp;</span></h3>
<p>The list below reflects <span>Sort Clauses</span>&nbsp;available in the =
<code>eZ\Publish\API\Repository\Values\Content\Query\<span>SortClause</span=
></code> namespace (it is also possible to <span class=3D"confluence-link">=
make a custom Sort Clause</span>):</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Arguments starting with "<code>?</code>" are optional.</p>
</div>
</div>
